[h1]Stop clicking "Allow" after every raid.[/h1]

[b]Smart Allow[/b] automatically unforbids dropped items with full control over what gets allowed. Weapons, apparel, resources -- all handled. Drugs? Excluded by default.

[hr][/hr]

[h1]Features[/h1]

[list]
[*] [b]Auto-allow all forbidden items[/b] -- weapons, apparel, food, resources, everything
[*] [b]11 category toggles[/b] -- control exactly what gets auto-allowed in mod settings
[*] [b]Drugs excluded by default[/b] -- raiders' yayo stays forbidden unless you opt in
[*] [b]Combat-aware[/b] -- holds auto-allow during active raids so pawns don't run into firefights
[*] [b]Home zone filter[/b] -- optionally only auto-allow items within your home zone
[*] [b]Double-forbid = permanent[/b] -- forbid something twice and Smart Allow stops touching it
[*] [b]Zero performance impact[/b] -- lightweight scan, no per-tick overhead
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h1]Category Toggles[/h1]

Open mod settings to configure. Each category can be independently enabled or disabled:

[list]
[*] Weapons -- ON by default
[*] Apparel -- ON by default
[*] [b]Drugs -- OFF by default[/b]
[*] Food -- ON by default
[*] Resources (steel, wood, components) -- ON by default
[*] Corpses -- ON by default
[*] Stone chunks and slag -- ON by default
[*] Body parts and bionics -- ON by default
[*] Medicine -- ON by default
[*] Artifacts and special items -- ON by default
[*] Everything else -- ON by default
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h1]How Double-Forbid Works[/h1]

[list]
[*] A weapon drops during combat -- RimWorld auto-forbids it
[*] Smart Allow unforbids it after combat ends
[*] You decide you don't want THAT weapon -- you forbid it manually
[*] Smart Allow sees you forbade something it already allowed -- marks it [b]permanently forbidden[/b]
[*] Smart Allow never touches that item again
[/list]

This lets you keep specific items forbidden without disabling entire categories.

[hr][/hr]

[h1]Compatibility[/h1]

[list]
[*] Works with any mod
[*] Does not conflict with [b]Allow Tool[/b] -- they solve different problems
[*] Safe to add or remove mid-save
[/list]

[h1]Requirements[/h1]
[list]
[*] RimWorld 1.6+
[*] [url=https://steamcommunity.com/workshop/filedetails/?id=2009463077]Harmony[/url]
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h1]Languages[/h1]
English, German, Chinese Simplified, Japanese, Korean, Russian, Spanish

